26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: drm_flip_work.c,v 1.3 2018/08/27 04:58:19 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include <linux/export.h>
30
31#include <drm/drmP.h>
32#include <drm/drm_flip_work.h>
33
34/**
35 * drm_flip_work_allocate_task - allocate a flip-work task
36 * @data: data associated to the task
37 * @flags: allocator flags
38 *
39 * Allocate a drm_flip_task object and attach private data to it.
40 */
41struct drm_flip_task *drm_flip_work_allocate_task(void *data, gfp_t flags)
42{
43 struct drm_flip_task *task;
44
45 task = kzalloc(sizeof(*task), flags);
46 if (task)
47 task->data = data;
48
49 return task;
50}
51EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_flip_work_allocate_task);
52
53/**
54 * drm_flip_work_queue_task - queue a specific task
55 * @work: the flip-work
56 * @task: the task to handle
57 *
58 * Queues task, that will later be run (passed back to drm_flip_func_t
59 * func) on a work queue after drm_flip_work_commit() is called.
60 */
61void drm_flip_work_queue_task(struct drm_flip_work *work,
62 struct drm_flip_task *task)
63{
64 unsigned long flags;
65
66 spin_lock_irqsave(&work->lock, flags);
67 list_add_tail(&task->node, &work->queued);
68 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&work->lock, flags);
69}
70EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_flip_work_queue_task);
71
72/**
73 * drm_flip_work_queue - queue work
74 * @work: the flip-work
75 * @val: the value to queue
76 *
77 * Queues work, that will later be run (passed back to drm_flip_func_t
78 * func) on a work queue after drm_flip_work_commit() is called.
79 */
80void drm_flip_work_queue(struct drm_flip_work *work, void *val)
81{
82 struct drm_flip_task *task;
83
84 task = drm_flip_work_allocate_task(val,
85 drm_can_sleep() ? GFP_KERNEL : GFP_ATOMIC);
86 if (task) {
87 drm_flip_work_queue_task(work, task);
88 } else {
89 DRM_ERROR("%s could not allocate task!\n", work->name);
90 work->func(work, val);
91 }
92}
93EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_flip_work_queue);
94
95/**
96 * drm_flip_work_commit - commit queued work
97 * @work: the flip-work
98 * @wq: the work-queue to run the queued work on
99 *
100 * Trigger work previously queued by drm_flip_work_queue() to run
101 * on a workqueue. The typical usage would be to queue work (via
102 * drm_flip_work_queue()) at any point (from vblank irq and/or
103 * prior), and then from vblank irq commit the queued work.
104 */
105void drm_flip_work_commit(struct drm_flip_work *work,
106 struct workqueue_struct *wq)
107{
108 unsigned long flags;
109
110 spin_lock_irqsave(&work->lock, flags);
111 list_splice_tail(&work->queued, &work->commited);
112 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&work->queued);
113 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&work->lock, flags);
114 queue_work(wq, &work->worker);
115}
116EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_flip_work_commit);
117
118static void flip_worker(struct work_struct *w)
119{
120 struct drm_flip_work *work = container_of(w, struct drm_flip_work, worker);
121 struct list_head tasks;
122 unsigned long flags;
123
124 while (1) {
125 struct drm_flip_task *task, *tmp;
126
127 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&tasks);
128 spin_lock_irqsave(&work->lock, flags);
129 list_splice_tail(&work->commited, &tasks);
130 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&work->commited);
131 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&work->lock, flags);
132
133 if (list_empty(&tasks))
134 break;
135
136 list_for_each_entry_safe(task, tmp, &tasks, node) {
137 work->func(work, task->data);
138 kfree(task);
139 }
140 }
141}
142
143/**
144 * drm_flip_work_init - initialize flip-work
145 * @work: the flip-work to initialize
146 * @name: debug name
147 * @func: the callback work function
148 *
149 * Initializes/allocates resources for the flip-work
150 */
151void drm_flip_work_init(struct drm_flip_work *work,
152 const char *name, drm_flip_func_t func)
153{
154 work->name = name;
155 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&work->queued);
156 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&work->commited);
157 spin_lock_init(&work->lock);
158 work->func = func;
159
160 INIT_WORK(&work->worker, flip_worker);
161}
162EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_flip_work_init);
163
164/**
165 * drm_flip_work_cleanup - cleans up flip-work
166 * @work: the flip-work to cleanup
167 *
168 * Destroy resources allocated for the flip-work
169 */
170void drm_flip_work_cleanup(struct drm_flip_work *work)
171{
172 WARN_ON(!list_empty(&work->queued) || !list_empty(&work->commited));
173}
174EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_flip_work_cleanup);
